RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 45. Maiden Special Weight Purse 36000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EVERLASTING SPIRIT dueled inside, shifted outside of the leader at the half-mile pole, vied in the two path and was clear, holding command while drifting out under mild urging. WAR TRINKETS bid four wide at the half-mile pole, bid at the quarter pole but couldn't get to the winner and faltered. LADY ARTIST was unrushed early, angled to the seven path at the eighth pole and gained the show late. SOLRUN pressed the early pace in the three path, settled, bid at the three-eighths pole, then gave way in the stretch. THREE COATS improved position late. CATRINA PARTNER bid four wide at the half-mile pole, then gave way in the stretch. WHAT ABOUT NOW led outside of the winner, took the rail near the half-mile pole, led inside, then gave way in the stretch. RUBY GIRL faded.

ENTRY.NAME: What About Now
ENTRY.COMMENT: led outside winner,took rail1/2,gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Ruby Girl
ENTRY.OWNER: Jimenez Normando Southwest Racing Stables Inc and Chavez Roberto

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIRE BRYAN chased the pace from the three path into the turn, bid three wide nearing the five-sixteenth pole, cleared into the lane and held. KNICKS STORY raced in the four path through the turn and into the lane, had aim on the winner after straightening then could not gain on that one while finishing clear for the place spot. EL CUERVO FELIS was off to an awkward start, moved up to race behind a four rival wall through the turn, bid three wide an in the vacated path of the winner, had sights on the top one then weakened late while drifting in. MINING CAMP vied for the lead two wide through the turn then gave way through the lane. OUR MAJESTIC was in the two path through the turn and never factored. SECRET HONOR was in the three or four path through the turn and made no impact. B ADMAN vied for the lead along the inside through the turn and gave way entering the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: El Cuervo Felis
ENTRY.COMMENT: awkward start, 2-3path turn, bid 3wd upper, drifted in late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 79. Allowance Purse 41000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 16 Allowed 3 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances). If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KNIGHT'S MOVE was unrushed inside, raced in the two path in the stretch, moved to the rail late and rallied, being clear at the wire under mild urging. SECRET'S IMAGE stalked the pace in the three path, bid at the eighth pole but couldn't hold off the winner. MUSTY RED pressed the pace inside, bid late and was caught. KILLER HOTROD stalked the pace in the two path, settled, then had no late bid. LOOKING GOOD LEWIS led inside before giving way late. FOREVER FRIENDS broke outward at the start, then was no factor. CASPER JUSTICE stalked the pace in the four path before fading. BIG BOY VICK was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Knight's Move
ENTRY.OWNER: McLean Warren Gene and Deerfield Farm Racing

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 25000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 121 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RUNTOLIVE was off alertly to gain the lead at once, continued with the lead while put under pressure through the turn and racing in the two path, shook clear into the lane then widened to the wire. PARLAY CHARLIE prompted the pace three wide through the turn, came into the lane with aim on the leader, could not gain on that one and just lasted for the show spot. BEAUTIFUL SUMMER was unhurried while off the inside, moved through the three or four path through late turn and into the lane then continued with good energy to be closing in and just missing the place spot while not a threat to the top one. HIGH SISU pressed winner two wide through the turn and into the lane and weakened. MORNING GORDITA tracked the pace along the inside through the turn then lacked a closing bid. ANGEL ON FIRE was in the two path through the turn when near the back, drifted to the seven path through the lane, was urged right-handed to drift back into the five path and never was factor. PURR TIGER showed speed into the turn when in the four path then was suddenly done after mid-turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Runtolive
ENTRY.COMMENT: alert start, pace 2path, gaining on place

ENTRY.NAME: Angel On Fire
ENTRY.OWNER: James Gary V and Lewis Robert E

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 5 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 1/16 on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet ).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER LUXE dueled outside of a rival, bid on the far turn to go clear and held sway under mild urging. ENGLISHED trailed to the stretch and bid late in the three path. SKYVIEW DRIVE dueled inside before giving way on the far turn. STARLIT SOFI stalked the pace in the three path before fading on the far turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 98. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 16 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (C laiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Estimating Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OPTIMAL COURAGE chased the three rival duel through the turn while in the three path, tipped into the four or five path for the drive, gained a clear lead just outside the eighth pole then was under a drive to hold. TALE OF FAME saved ground through the turn, came off the inside into the lane, split rivals near the eighth pole while three wide, continued with good energy while inching up on the winner in a good effort. BEVERLY PARK unhurried through the turn while in the two or three path, was in the five path when gaining momentum near the eighth pole and was inching up to the wire. EL ROSILLO saved ground through the turn and into the lane, bid and was a serious threat with an eighth to go then could not sustain the effort. TRIKITRAKI was in the three path through the turn while in mid-pack, came into the lane from the five or six path and finished evenly. VIOLENT GIGI was in the three path through the turn when near the back, came into the lane from the eight path and moved up while not a threat. SILVER MOON ROAD vied for the lead from between rivals through the turn and gave way. I'M WIDE AWAKE vied for the lead along the inside of two others through the turn and was empty turning into the lane. FENESTRA raced three wide into a fast pace into the turn, continued three wide through the turn and retreated through the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Tale of Fame
ENTRY.OWNER: Spiess Stable LLC and Klopp, Randy

ENTRY.OWNER: Wright Don R and Wright Pepper

ENTRY.OWNER: Lindaman Byron D and Silva Racing LLC

ENTRY.NAME: Violent Gigi
ENTRY.OWNER: Contreras Stable Inc and Desperado Racing LLC

(PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEEN CONTENDER was unrushed early, commenced a four wide rally at the three-eighths pole and drew off under mild urging. MORNING ANGEL was unrushed early, rallied four wide through the backstretch, was clear in the stretch but couldn't hold off the winner. DREAM TRAP stalked the pace in the four path, bid at the half-mile pole, then faltered in the stretch. CANDY KICK raced in the three path with no late bid. LA DAME DE FER vied in the two path for a half mile before giving way. CINDERELLA STORY stalked the pace in the three path before fading. CLASSY DREAM vied early inside before giving way. A STAR FOR CORA pressed the pace in the three path before fading.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ACTION SEEKER chased the pace from the four path into the turn, bid in mid-turn to get nearest the leader, cleared inside the eighth pole then held while being kept to the task. WOODYTHEBIDSPOTTER chased the pace into the turn, raced four wide through late turn, continued in the five path through the lane and was inching up to the end. INFINITY'S WARRIOR raced in the two or three path through the turn when never far back, continued in the four path through the lane and stayed on well to be best of the rest. REDHILL saved ground through late turn, came off the inside into the lane, gained momentum once straightened then rallied while in the four or five path late. HAY MOON chased the pace along the inside through the turn and into the lane and tired. PRINCE OF PENNIES was off to an alert start, set the pace under pressure into the turn, vied for the lead into the lane then faded. TRUE PRODIGY was close up early while in the three path, began to lose ground after mid-turn then was empty through the lane. BEAU DAY saved ground along the inside and lost ground. MUD PUDDLE was outrun while in the two path through the turn. BOXSTER in the five path through the turn when near the back, came into the lane from mid-track and tired.
